review_blob: Standard lager colour, quite a lot of pretty dense foam that dissipates unevenly. Easy drinkable, fruity, hoppy, just a bit metallic taste noticeable. Leaves a nice bittery aftertaste. Pretty much a standard lager. 12/20
Watery, thin, weird flavour-doesnt tastw like beer at times, metallic and very sweet aftertaste. However its still better than some of other Lidl beers (alcoholic too). I don?t reccomend it. 3/20

Brown but not dark brown appearance and a little of quickly dissipating foam.Nice balanced taste. Chocolaty,caramel, earthy notes. No metallic taste detected. Easy drinking, wonderful and kind of longlasting aftertaste. Reccomended, 17/20
No special aroma/appearance. Watery, weak taste, weird metallic finish, i wonder what they made this beer from. It would be drinkable if it hadnt such metallic aftertaste. 4/10

Nice fruity aroma when poured, kind of degrades over time
Only a little of quickly dissipating foam, fruity, malty,metallic taste, medium bitter aftertaste. Interesting aroma but nohing special going on. 11/20

Dark,near black colour, not much foam
Tastes of caramel, slightly chocolate,coffee,.. Not much going on..Slightly bitter aftertaste, quite carbonated
